      "content": "Typically, debris such as insects, dirt, or even small debris from the plane's external parts can enter and block the pitot tube opening. But it can also be more unexpected. For instance, ice formation in colder climates can clog the tube, especially if there's an accumulation of moisture. Sometimes, even small birds or insects can get caught, leading to a blockage. Additionally, mechanical impacts or wear and tear over time could also lead to debris accumulation. Any foreign material entering the pitot tube can disrupt the airflow and therefore affect the accuracy of the airspeed measurement.",
